& [SLMPrimerSchemaVersioningContract] is the contract for stable primer schema identity
  + [contract_uuid] is 431ca8d4-72f0-4780-a4d0-d48f7fd16f5e
  + [slice_id] is SLM-48
  + [depends_on] is SLM_Primer_Rendering_Contract, SLM_Primer_Compaction_Budget_Contract
  + [status] is verified_wsl

  & [Purpose] is to make SLM primers safe for machine re-ingestion across prototype changes
    = must: expose a stable schema id in every primer JSON object
    = must: expose a concrete schema version in every primer JSON object
    = must: expose a compatibility floor for readers that accept earlier v0 primers
    = must: list stable required fields so downstream consumers can validate primer shape
    = must: preserve the existing version field as a legacy short identifier during v0
    - never: remove or silently rename a required primer field without a schema version change

  & [SchemaIdentity] is the v0 primer identity surface
    + [schema_id] is slm_primer
    + [schema_version] is 0.1.0
    + [compatibility_floor] is 0.1.0
    + [legacy_version] is slm_primer_v0

  & [RequiredFields] are the stable v0 primer fields
    + [field] is version
    + [field] is schema
    + [field] is input_ref
    + [field] is graph_ref
    + [field] is subjects
    + [field] is actions
    + [field] is relations
    + [field] is modifiers
    + [field] is constraints
    + [field] is uncertainty
    + [field] is wobble
    + [field] is compact_evidence
    + [field] is compaction
    + [field] is lineage_refs
    + [field] is sop_rendering

  & [CompatibilityPolicy] is the migration expectation
    = must: add optional fields without changing compatibility_floor when older readers can ignore them
    = must: increment schema_version when field meaning, requiredness, or interpretation changes
    = must: increase compatibility_floor only when older readers cannot safely consume the primer
    = must: keep primer evidence refs normalized before schema publication
    - never: treat compact_evidence as exhaustive unless compaction metadata says no evidence was omitted

  & [RuntimeProjection] is the Rust source surface
    + [module] is slm_rust/src/primer.rs PrimerSchemaInfo
    + [module] is slm_rust/src/primer.rs SLM_PRIMER_SCHEMA_ID
    + [module] is slm_rust/src/primer.rs SLM_PRIMER_SCHEMA_VERSION
    + [module] is slm_rust/src/primer.rs primer_schema_info
    + [proof_route] is Rust serialization test and WSL cargo test

  ! [Slice48SourceComplete] is accepted
    @ [source_gate] passed python slm_project/tools/slm_source_gate_check.py
    @ [wsl_cargo_test] passed 17 tests through CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/home/pinky/slm_rust_target and linker=/home/pinky/bin/zigcc
    @ [self_check] passed slm_self_check
    @ [demo_schema_id] is slm_primer
    @ [demo_schema_version] is 0.1.0
    @ [demo_compatibility_floor] is 0.1.0
    @ [demo_required_field_count] is 15
